CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 10, 1957, pg. A17 reads: "Lincoln Men and their wives got together at the Frogs' formal for this photo. Left to right: James Dorsey, Mrs. Jesse Gloster and Mr. Gloster of Houston, Tex.; Mrs. W. Beverly Carter, wife of The Courier publisher; Franklin Williams, director, NAACP Freedom Fund; Mrs. WIlliams and Mr. Carter.  The men were all classmates at Lincoln University (Pa.)"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: James Dorsey, Mrs. Jesse Gloster, Mr. Gloster, Mrs. W. Beverly Carter, Mr. and Mrs. Franklin Williams, and W. Beverly Carter, standing in Gateway Plaza for FROGS Formal Ball
